  "text": "The TCP assay described by [CITATION_1] is most widely used test for detection of biofilm formation. We screened all strains for their ability to form biofilm by TCP method with some modifications. Each test included biofilm formation control. Bacterial biofilm formation properties were well described by [CITATION_2] . Antibiofilm activity was calculated in form of the biofilm inhibitory concentration (BIC) at 50 and 90 percent.",
